SERVER CREATION

BASIC COMMANDS

1)Creating package.json - npm init
2)Install express - npm i express
3)Install JWT - npm i jsonwebtoken
4)Install mongoose - npm i mongoose

BASIC STEPS

1. Creating a folder
2. Creating a package.json file
3. Install express
4. Creating index.js file
5. Import express inside the index.js
6. Create an app using the express
7. Setup port number
8. Resolving HTTP requests 
9. HTTP response code
    1xx - Information
    2xx - Success
    3xx - Redirection
    4xx - Client Error
    5xx - Server Error

10. JWT(JSON web token) token- for authentication
    sign()

11. middleware
    1. Application specific middleware -  request ayyakkumbol edakk loading aavathe loading ... nn nikkunnathinaann
       ath pazhayath pole aavaan next(); kodukkuka
    2. Router specific middleware - token validate - verify()

    req.body.token - changed to req.headers.['']  bodyil kodukkunna token header il kodukkuka oru name vech

12. DataBase integration
     install mongoose